bergmark_d wrote:
...

&gt; What I would like:  CandidateURI has an AList (null by default).  The
&gt; CreateCandidateURI method can be overridden (i.e. it has protected
&gt; status) so that applications can stuff stuff (!!) into the candidate&#39;s
&gt; AList.  When a CrawlURI is instantiated from a CandidateURI, it should
&gt; *merge* its Core Attribute thingies with whatever AList is in the
&gt; CandidateURI.
&gt;
We figured (smile).

&gt; Given this implementation, it would be easy for apps to arrange for
&gt; parent URIs to pass info to their children.  And that would be good.
&gt;
Try it now.  The AList has been moved back into the CandidateURI and put 
behind accessors/getters. CrawlURIs made from CandidateURIs inside in 
Frontier will have whatever was in the CandidateURI AList when CrawlURI 
was created.

Refactorings to come will probably include adding a flag on the AList 
setters so you can say whether your data is transient or not -- i.e. 
whether it can be discarded at the end of a pass through the processing 
chain (may also be whether or not value should be serialized too TBD) -- 
and the Postselector will probably be broken in two with one piece 
focused on scope-checking and the other on scheduling.

Yours,
St.Ack

